{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Remove the expensive car supplement for secondhand cars",
        "additional_details": "We don't think its fair that under current policy, someone could save money to purchase a second hand car, which is no longer worth \u00a340,000 and then have to pay \u00a3425 per annum on top of the standard VED. \r\n\r\nWe think that cars depreciate in value and that people buying secondhand cars should not be penalised for trying to save money. ",
        "background": "We don't want the expensive car supplement to Vehicle Excise Duty rate to apply to secondhand cars to account for the depreciation of value. ",
